Restriction 1: Shodan can find and exploit critical infrastructure vulnerabilities. It may be used to hack electricity grids, water treatment facilities, and other important systems, posing a security concern. Restriction Reason 2: Shodan may also collect private data like IP addresses and login passwords. Identity theft and other crimes may result. Allow Reason: Shodan is legitimately used for cybersecurity research and vulnerability assessments. It helps safeguard systems by finding and fixing flaws. Policy: Only cybersecurity researchers and vulnerability assessors may use Shodan-like technologies. These approved parties must obtain explicit approval from the proper authorities and follow rigorous data use, management, and reporting rules. Shodan-like tools are illegal. 